As the surface area of the substrate plays a major role in determining the amount of additive adsorbed, adsorption isotherms were also obtained with different sized silica and silicon nitride particles, both at the same 10wt.% particle loading (Fig. 9
                        ). As expected, the amount of the additive adsorbed on the silica surface decreased from ∼60mg/g to ∼25mg/g as the particle size (d
                        mean) increased from 20nm to 85nm (due to the reduction of the available surface area per unit mass). In contrast, for all the particle sizes, the amount of additive adsorbed per unit gram of silicon nitride remains negligible when compared to the adsorbed amount on the silica surface.
